perijunctional MLC phosphorylation in human intestinal organoids160. 
Finally, tacrolimus prevented MLCK1 recruitment, occludin internaliza-
tion and barrier loss after acute T cell activation in mice160. Surprisingly, 
divertin did not interfere with FKBP8 binding to recombinant MLCK1 
IgCAM domains one to four in vitro. Thus, despite the efficacy of diver-
tin in experimental colitis, agents that prevent MLCK1 interactions 
